The paper proposes a machine learning model to identify escort ads that are likely linked to sex trafficking. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to analyze the text in the ads, which suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of identifying illegal activity, which could fall under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed model uses deep learning techniques, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or computer vision (cs.CV).
